unittitle_ssm: Queens County Court of General Sessions of the Peace record
abstract_ssm: A decision issued by the Queens County Court of General Sessions of the Peace, dated 1799. The case in question concerned a John Schenck of the town of North Hempstead, Long Island, who sought the court's approval to manumit (or free) an enslaved African-American man named Prince.
